WEBVTT

00:02.030 --> 00:04.476
- YOU'RE FUNNY.
YOU'RE PRETI'Y.

00:04.590 --> 00:06.899
YOU'RE NICE.
I LIKE TALKING TO YOU.

00:07.000 --> 00:08.376
- LET'S MOVE IN TOGETHER.

00:08.490 --> 00:11.038
- I'M RUNNING
FOR STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT.

00:11.140 --> 00:12.243
I AM GOING
TO GET THE SCHOOL BOARD

00:12.350 --> 00:13.658
TO BRING BACK
THE VENDING MACHINE.

00:13.770 --> 00:15.101
- ZEEK BRAVERMAN.
- RYAN YORK.

00:15.220 --> 00:16.835
- SO YOU WERE
IN AFGHANISTAN, RIGHT?

00:16.940 --> 00:18.419
- YEAH.

00:18.530 --> 00:20.043
- YOU'LL NEED TO TELL US
THAT YOUR FOCUS

00:20.150 --> 00:21.970
IS 100%
ON YOUR CLIENTS.

00:22.090 --> 00:23.318
- I QUIT.

00:23.430 --> 00:24.636
- I WENT TO THE DOCTOR
FOR MY YEARLY MAMMOGRAM.

00:24.740 --> 00:28.369
THEY FOUND SOMETHING--
- THEY FOUND A SMALL TUMOR.

00:32.300 --> 00:33.403
- I LOVE YOU ALL SO MUCH.

00:33.510 --> 00:35.819
THERE'S SOMETHING
THAT I NEED TO TELL YOU.

00:40.140 --> 00:42.028
- MAMA, IF YOU WANNA
SIT DOWN--

00:42.140 --> 00:43.619
- CAN YOU PLEASE
GO SIT DOWN?

00:43.730 --> 00:45.209
YOU'RE MAKING ME NERVOUS--
- I'M SAYING YOU CAN SIT DOWN,

00:45.320 --> 00:46.719
AND I'LL DO THE WORK.
- I NEED MY PERSONAL SPACE,

00:46.830 --> 00:48.001
HADDIE, I'M TOTALLY FINE.

00:48.110 --> 00:49.975
- WELL, I'M HERE TO HELP YOU,
AND YOU NEED

00:50.080 --> 00:51.286
TO GIVE ME SOMETHING
TO DO.

00:51.390 --> 00:52.698
- GIVE YOUR DAD A HUG.
- YEAH, GIVE ME A HUG.

00:52.810 --> 00:54.801
- NO. LIKE, I CAN DO ANYTHING
THAT YOU DON'T WAN NA DO,

00:54.910 --> 00:58.459
LIKE, TAKE NORA TO SCHOOL, OR--
- HONEY, I PROMISE YOU,

00:58.570 --> 01:00.743
I'M TOTALLY FINE.
WHAT I WANT YOU TO FOCUS ON

01:00.850 --> 01:04.081
IS YOUR MAKEUP WORK, OKAY?
YOU'VE ALREADY MISSED A WEEK

01:04.200 --> 01:05.155
OF CLASS,
AND THAT'S FREAKING ME OUT--

01:05.270 --> 01:06.749
- NO, A WEEK
DOESN'T MA'I'I'ER.

01:06.850 --> 01:08.431
I COULD TAKE A SEMESTER OFF,
AND IT WOULDN'T MA'I'I'ER.

01:08.550 --> 01:09.687
- YOU'RE NOT TAKING
A SEMESTER OFF.

01:09.790 --> 01:11.064
- MAYBE I SHOULD
DO THAT.

01:11.170 --> 01:13.092
- OKAY, HADDIE,
WE APPRECIATE THE OFFER.

01:13.210 --> 01:14.780
IT'S NOT NECESSARY.
- I'M NOT GONNA TAKE IT

01:14.900 --> 01:16.106
AS A "NO,"
AS A CLOSED SUBJECT.

01:16.210 --> 01:19.065
YOU CAN'T JUST SAY NO.
- I'M GONNA BE FINE, OKAY?

01:19.180 --> 01:20.966
DR. BEDSLOE
IS REALLY OPTIMISTIC.

01:21.080 --> 01:23.219
- DON'T SAY "NO."
WE NEED OPTIONS FOR THINGS

01:23.320 --> 01:24.867
THAT CAN HAPPEN.
SEMESTER'S TAKEN OFF.

01:24.980 --> 01:26.902
- HADDIE, WHY IS THIS
IN MY SEAT?

01:27.010 --> 01:28.216
- MAX, PLEASE.
- MAX, I'LL PICK THAT UP

01:28.320 --> 01:30.015
BECAUSE I'M HELPFUL.
- JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE HOME

01:30.120 --> 01:31.348
DOESN'T MEAN YOU CAN
STEAL MY SEAT.

01:31.470 --> 01:32.391
- OKAY, JUST A SECOND, MAX.
I WANNA REMIND YOU

01:32.500 --> 01:33.421
THAT ON WEDNESDAY,
YOUR MOTHER AND I

01:33.540 --> 01:35.531
ARE GONNA BE
IN THE HOSPITAL ALL DAY.

01:35.640 --> 01:37.119
GRANDMA AND GRANDPA
ARE GONNA DROP YOU OFF,

01:37.230 --> 01:38.743
PICK YOU UP FROM SCHOOL.
- ALL RIGHT, TELL HIM

01:38.850 --> 01:40.294
PICK ME UP AT 4:30,
NOT 3:30.

01:40.410 --> 01:41.638
- HOW COME?
- WHY IS THAT?

01:41.750 --> 01:43.570
- WELL, BECAUSE IT'S GONNA
TAKE THEM A LONG TIME

01:43.680 --> 01:44.783
TO COUNT THE VOTES.

01:44.890 --> 01:46.471
AND I WANNA BE THERE RIGHT
WHEN I'M MADE PRESIDENT.

01:46.580 --> 01:48.514
- WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
THE ELECTION IS ON WEDNESDAY?

01:48.620 --> 01:49.848
HOW DID WE NOT KNOW THIS?
- I DON'T KNOW.

01:49.970 --> 01:51.130
WE'LL--
- WE MISS FOURTH PERIOD

01:51.240 --> 01:53.276
SO THAT ALL THE CANDIDATES
CAN GIVE THEIR SPEECHES,

01:53.380 --> 01:55.245
AND I'M LAST UP,
WHICH I THINK GIVES ME AN EDGE

01:55.350 --> 01:56.863
BECAUSE I'M GONNA
BE THE LAST THING PEOPLE HEAR

01:56.970 --> 01:57.902
BEFORE THEY GO
TO VOTE.

01:58.010 --> 01:59.147
- YOU'RE DOING A SPEECH?

01:59.250 --> 02:00.558
- YES, I AM.
NO, I DON'T WANT THIS BACON NOW.

02:00.670 --> 02:02.285
I'M GONNA GET SOME CEREAL.
- OKAY, SOUNDS

02:02.390 --> 02:03.596
LIKE A GOOD IDEA, BUD.

02:03.700 --> 02:05.327
- WHY DID YOU MAKE ME
CHANGE THE SURGERY DATE?

02:05.430 --> 02:06.328
WE COULD'VE BEEN THERE.
- I DIDN'T MAKE YOU

02:06.430 --> 02:07.397
CHANGE THE SURGERY DATE.
I DID NOT.

02:13.340 --> 02:15.365
- HEY.
- HEY.

02:15.480 --> 02:16.549
- HOW'S IT GOIN'?
- HEY, LISTEN.

02:16.650 --> 02:18.743
I'M JUST FINISHING UP
TH ESE CONTRACTS

02:18.860 --> 02:20.088
FOR THAT BAND COMMON ROTATION,
SO ALL YOU'RE GONNA

02:20.200 --> 02:21.235
HAVE TO DO IS HAND THEM
TO THEIR MANAGER

02:21.340 --> 02:22.329
WHEN HE WALKS
THROUGH THE DOOR, OKAY?

02:22.450 --> 02:24.782
- OKAY, PERFECT.
- ALL RIGHT.

02:24.900 --> 02:26.959
- WHAT ELSE?
- UH, NOTHIN'.

02:27.070 --> 02:28.173
I'M JUST TRYING
TO GET ALL THIS DONE

02:28.280 --> 02:29.554
BECAUSE I DON'T WANNA BE
OBSESSING ABOUT WORK

02:29.660 --> 02:31.173
WHEN I'M WAITING FOR KRISTINA
TO GET OUT OF SURGERY,

02:31.280 --> 02:32.861
YOU KNOW?
- RIGHT. OKAY.

02:32.980 --> 02:35.619
- [exhales]
- CAN I HELP YOU WITH ANYTHING?

02:35.740 --> 02:37.355
- NO. I'M ALL RIGHT.

02:37.460 --> 02:39.906
- WHAT'S GOIN' ON
BACK HERE?

02:40.020 --> 02:42.705
MM-HMM.

02:42.810 --> 02:44.744
YEP.

02:44.850 --> 02:46.226
- WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?
- WELL, YOU'RE CARRYIN' A LOT

02:46.330 --> 02:47.399
OF STRESS BACK HERE.
- YEAH, I AM.

02:47.510 --> 02:49.569
- THERE'S LIKE SIX
OR SEVEN KNOTS JUST RIGHT

02:49.680 --> 02:52.240
IN THIS AREA RIGHT HERE.
IT'S REALLY COMMON FOR GUYS.

02:52.340 --> 02:54.570
THEY GET REALLY STRESSED OUT,
AND THEY START--

02:54.690 --> 02:56.783
- RIGHT, OW, OKAY,
CAN YOU--CAN YOU--CAN YOU STOP?

02:56.900 --> 02:58.470
OKAY.
CAN YOU STOP?

02:58.590 --> 02:59.921
- AND THEN LET ME JUST GET
IN HERE REALLY QUICK.

03:00.040 --> 03:01.109
- OW!
- YOU FEEL THAT?

03:01.210 --> 03:03.383
- CROSBY, GOD! GET OFF!
- FINE!

03:03.490 --> 03:04.934
I'M JUST TRYIN'
TO HELP.

03:05.040 --> 03:06.905
- OKAY.
THANK YOU.

03:07.010 --> 03:10.184
- WHAT CAN I DO TO ALLEVIATE
SOME OF THIS STRESS FOR YA?

03:10.290 --> 03:12.520
- NEVER TOUCH ME AGAIN.
LET'S START WITH THAT.

03:12.640 --> 03:14.119
- OKAY.
UH, BUT SERIOUSLY,

03:14.220 --> 03:16.154
IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN--I CAN DO?

03:16.260 --> 03:17.227
- LISTEN, CROSBY,
I REALLY APPRECIATE IT,

03:17.330 --> 03:18.558
BUT I'VE GOT NOTHING
FOR YOU TO DO.

03:18.680 --> 03:20.705
- OKAY, WELL, JULIE
IS MAKIN' QUINOA MUFFINS,

03:20.820 --> 03:22.014
AND MOM AND DAD
ARE WATCHIN' THE KIDS,

03:22.130 --> 03:24.644
AND I'M DOIN' NOTHING,
SO I--YOU KNOW,

03:24.750 --> 03:26.263
I FEEL A LITTLE GUILTY--
- ALL RIGHT, LISTEN TO ME.

03:26.370 --> 03:28.372
SINCE YOU OFFERED--OTIS.
YOU COULD TAKE OTIS

03:28.480 --> 03:29.959
TO THE DOG PARK.
HE'S BEEN REALLY NEGLECTED.

03:30.070 --> 03:31.094
THAT'D BE GREAT.
YEAH.

03:31.210 --> 03:33.371
- ADAM, THAT'S
LIKE A LITTLE KID FAVOR.

03:33.480 --> 03:34.583
THAT'S WHAT YOU'D
GIVE A LITTLE KID--

03:34.690 --> 03:35.554
- NO, IT'S NOT.
THIS IS THE FAMILY DOG.

03:35.660 --> 03:37.514
- I WANT A MAN-SIZED FAVOR.

03:37.630 --> 03:39.552
I WANNA DO SOMETHING
SUBSTANTIAL FOR YOU GUYS.

03:39.660 --> 03:42.595
- I DON'T HAVE ANY--
EVERYTHING'S COVERED.

03:42.700 --> 03:45.316
- OKAY, I WILL TAKE THE DOG
TO THE DOG PARK,

03:45.430 --> 03:46.909
BUT I WANNA DO
AT LEAST ONE THING

03:47.010 --> 03:49.945
THAT KRISTINA
WILL REMEMBER.

03:50.050 --> 03:51.426
- I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING.
- OOH!

03:51.540 --> 03:52.768
I OVERHEARD YOU TELLING AMBER
THAT YOU'RE GONNA ORDER

03:52.880 --> 03:54.222
HER FAVORITE TAKEOUT
ON THE DAY OF THE SURGERY.

03:54.330 --> 03:55.604
DO YOU WANT ME TO DO THAT?
I'LL ORDER FROM THERE,

03:55.710 --> 03:57.598
AND THEN I'LL PICK IT UP
AND BRING IT...

03:57.720 --> 03:59.290
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
- YOU JUST LET ME HANDLE IT?

03:59.410 --> 04:01.264
- THAT'S REALLY THOUGHTFUL.
THAT'D BE A BIG HELP.

04:01.370 --> 04:02.928
THEY DON'T DELIVER.
LA BERNADETI'E.

04:03.030 --> 04:05.134
- LA BERNADETI'E.
- AND YOU GOTTA GET US THE FOOD

04:05.240 --> 04:06.855
BY 6:00, BECAUSE KRISTINA
HAS TO FINISH EATING BY 8:00.

04:06.970 --> 04:09.416
- 6:00 PM. OKAY. DON'T EVEN
THINK ABOUT THIS AGAIN.

04:09.520 --> 04:12.694
THIS IS ALL GONNA HAPPEN,
ALL RIGHT?

04:12.800 --> 04:14.313
- THANKS, CROSBY.
I DO APPRECIATE IT.

04:14.420 --> 04:16.763
- THANKS FOR GIVIN' ME
SOMETHING.

04:16.870 --> 04:18.622
- [exhales]

04:20.670 --> 04:22.149
[rock music playing]
- WHOO

04:22.260 --> 04:24.660
SHE'S GOT STICKERS
ON HER LOCKER

04:24.780 --> 04:27.669
AND THE BOYS' NUMBERS THERE
IN MAGIC MARKER

04:27.780 --> 04:29.941
I'M HUNGRY
AND THE HUNGER WILL LINGER

04:30.060 --> 04:31.459
- WHAT?

04:31.580 --> 04:33.605
- ARE--ARE YOU SICK?
- NO.

04:33.720 --> 04:35.608
- THEN WHY AREN'T YOU PACKING?
IT'S MOVING DAY.

04:35.720 --> 04:37.688
MARK'S GONNA BE HERE
WITH THE TRUCK

04:37.790 --> 04:39.610
IN, LIKE, 20 MINUTES, SWEETIE.
LET'S GO.

04:39.720 --> 04:41.688
- ALL RIGHT, WELL, I NEED
MORE TIME THAN 20 MINUTES.

04:41.790 --> 04:43.519
- YOU NEED MORE TIME?
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY MORE TIME.

04:43.620 --> 04:45.030
WHAT DO YOU NEED HELP WITH--
- OKAY, MOM.

04:45.140 --> 04:46.311
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO DO THIS.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO PACK.

04:46.420 --> 04:47.694
HOW DO I WRAP THIS UP?

04:47.800 --> 04:50.109
ISN'T IT ALL JUST
GONNA GET SMASHED IN THE--

04:50.220 --> 04:52.211
- DO YOU WRAP--
DO YOU WRAP CHARLIE?

04:52.320 --> 04:55.073
H-HOW DO YOU WRAP CHARLIE?

04:55.190 --> 04:56.327
- YES.
- HONEY, YOU JUST PUT MAYBE

04:56.430 --> 04:58.216
A NICE LITI'LE SOFT--
- NO, BUT IT--NOW--

04:58.330 --> 04:59.285
- HE'LL BE FINE,
BECAUSE I'M GONNA PUT LOTS--

04:59.400 --> 05:00.662
- IS IT NOT GONNA
GET SMASHED IN THE--?

05:00.780 --> 05:02.327
- NO, SWEETIE.
WE'RE NOT GOING THAT FAR.

05:02.440 --> 05:04.362
COME ON.
- WHY ARE WE GOING AT ALL?

05:04.470 --> 05:06.017
- THE TRUCK
IS BY THE HOUR, OKAY?

05:06.130 --> 05:08.473
I TOOK THE DAY OFF OF WORK.
- WHY CAN'T I JUST STAY HERE?

05:08.580 --> 05:11.094
- [scoffs] DREW, WE TALKED
ABOUT THIS, ALL RIGHT?

05:11.200 --> 05:12.440
WE'RE ALL GONNA
LIVE TOGETHER

05:12.550 --> 05:14.541
AS A BIG, HAPPY FAMILY--
- OKAY, WHAT IF I DON'T WANT

05:14.650 --> 05:16.538
TO DO THAT MOM?
- DREW, REMEMBER

05:16.660 --> 05:18.867
WHEN WE CAME HERE
TO GRANDMA AND GRANDPA'S,

05:18.970 --> 05:20.062
AND YOU DIDN'T WANNA COME,
AND IT TURNED OUT

05:20.180 --> 05:21.579
TO BE THE BEST THING
WE EVER DID?

05:21.700 --> 05:22.769
- EXACTLY, SO WHY
ARE WE LEAVING?

05:22.870 --> 05:24.383
- TRUST ME.
- I DON'T WANNA GO.

05:24.490 --> 05:27.800
- SARAH!
TRUCK'S HERE!

05:27.910 --> 05:29.662
- I'LL BE RIGHT THERE!

05:34.090 --> 05:36.741
[groans] LOOK, HONEY, WE'LL TALK
ABOUT THIS IN THE CAR, OKAY?

05:36.850 --> 05:39.125
JUST GO AS FAST AS YOU CAN.
- ALL RIGHT.

05:39.230 --> 05:41.676
- HI.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

05:41.780 --> 05:43.919
- HEY.
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT SICK.

05:44.030 --> 05:46.407
- UH, WELL, I'M NOT SICK,
BUT I--YOU KNOW,

05:46.510 --> 05:47.829
I TOOK A SICK DAY.
- IT'S ALL RIGHT. IT'S OKAY.

05:47.930 --> 05:50.444
YEAH, I'M NOT MAD, NOT MAD.
I DON'T BLAME YA.

05:50.550 --> 05:51.858
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE WEIRDED OUT
ABOUT THE...

05:51.970 --> 05:54.621
- OH.
- THAT, UH, REGRE'I'I'ABLE THING

05:54.730 --> 05:56.038
THAT I DID.
I DON'T EVEN WANNA

05:56.140 --> 05:58.961
SAY IT OUT LOUD,
'CAUSE I FEEL LIKE A JACKASS?

05:59.080 --> 06:02.595
LOOK, JUST DON'T QUIT
BECAUSE I WAS STUPID, ALL RIGHT?

06:02.700 --> 06:04.804
- OH, MY GOD.
I'M NOT QUI'I'I'ING.

06:04.910 --> 06:08.698
I'M NOT QUI'I'I'ING.
I'M, UH--I'M MOVING.

06:08.810 --> 06:10.846
M--MOVING IN...
- OH!

06:10.950 --> 06:12.394
- WITH, UH, MARK--
HI, HONEY--

06:12.510 --> 06:18.506
AND, UH, DREW, AND--SO I JUST
TOOK A DAY TO MOVE.

06:18.610 --> 06:21.477
- HOW'S IT GOING?
- YEAH. WE'RE--HI.

06:21.580 --> 06:23.923
HANK JUST, UH--
- I GOT THE--YOU WANT THE--

06:24.030 --> 06:25.657
YOU WANT THE DOLLY?
I WAS GONNA GIVE HER THE DOLLY

06:25.760 --> 06:28.308
TO, UH, TO HELP YOU MOVE.
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU--

06:28.420 --> 06:30.797
YEAH, I'LL GET IT.
I GOT IT RIGHT IN THE VAN.

06:30.900 --> 06:31.821
- THANKS.
THAT WAS NICE OF HIM.

06:31.940 --> 06:34.147
- SEE YA.
- [growls] HEY! HEY, HEY!

06:34.250 --> 06:37.139
CAMERA GUY, GIVE ME A HAND
WITH THIS, WOULD YA?

06:37.250 --> 06:38.979
DON'T FORGET TO USE YOUR LEGS
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,

06:39.080 --> 06:40.286
YOUR AGE, YOUR BACK--
- WHERE ARE WE GOIN' WITH IT?

06:40.400 --> 06:41.492
- WE'RE GOIN' OVER
TO THIS U-HAUL THING.

06:41.600 --> 06:45.252
- THERE, MOM,
IT'S MY CLOTHES.

06:45.370 --> 06:47.565
- YOU'RE KIDDING?
HEY, MARK.

06:47.680 --> 06:50.888
[bag drops]
DON'T--HEY!

06:50.990 --> 06:54.505
DREW.
OH, MY GOD.

06:54.620 --> 06:57.305
[Lucy Schwartz's
When We Were Young]

06:59.480 --> 07:02.062
WHEN WE WERE YOUNG
WE WERE SMALL

07:02.180 --> 07:05.559
BUT WE DIDN'T
KNOW IT

07:05.660 --> 07:09.380
AH AHH AH

07:09.490 --> 07:12.209
WHEN YOU WERE HURT
YOU WOULD SMILE

07:12.320 --> 07:15.528
SO YOU DIDN'T
SHOW IT

07:15.640 --> 07:19.155
AH AHH AH

07:19.260 --> 07:23.264
AND I

07:23.370 --> 07:26.259
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

07:29.890 --> 07:33.337
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:34.900 --> 07:37.755
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:42.080 --> 07:42.648
- ALL RIGHT, LOOKS
LIKE YOU GUYS ARE ALL SET.

07:42.770 --> 07:45.000
SO THIS IS YOUR COPY.

07:45.110 --> 07:46.520
JUST TAKE IT HOME
AND MAKE SURE ALL,

07:46.630 --> 07:47.949
LIKE, THE BILLING STUFF
AND THE ADDRESS STUFF

07:48.050 --> 07:49.324
IS RIGHT, ALL RIGHT?

07:49.430 --> 07:51.113
COOL.
ALL RIGHT, TAKE IT EASY.

07:58.130 --> 07:59.119
- HEY.

07:59.230 --> 08:00.436
- HI.
- DO YOU REMEMBER ME?

08:00.540 --> 08:02.405
- [laughs] YES.
MY—-MY GRANDPA'S FRIEND.

08:02.510 --> 08:05.331
- RIGHT.
RYAN.

08:05.450 --> 08:06.826
- RYAN, HI. AMBER.

08:06.930 --> 08:10.411
- UH, SO, THIS IS, UH--
THIS IS THE PLACE YOU WORK?

08:10.520 --> 08:12.681
- YEAH.
- IT'S, UH, IT'S EVERY BIT

08:12.800 --> 08:14.347
AS NIFI'Y AS ZEEK
SAID IT WAS.

08:14.450 --> 08:16.270
- NIFI'Y.
THAT'S HIS FAVORITE.

08:16.390 --> 08:17.869
- "YOU SHOULD GO BY AND SEE
WHERE MY GRANDDAUGHTER WORKS.

08:17.980 --> 08:18.901
A REAL NIFI'Y OUTFIT
THEY GOT GOIN' ON."

08:19.010 --> 08:21.592
- [laughs] WELL,
IT IS A NIFTY OUTFIT.

08:21.700 --> 08:24.908
UH, WELL, COOL.
UM--

08:25.020 --> 08:27.773
ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN MUSIC?

08:27.880 --> 08:31.919
UH, I'M INTERESTED
IN YOU.

08:32.020 --> 08:33.601
- OH.

08:33.720 --> 08:35.608
THAT'S VERY DIRECT.

08:35.720 --> 08:37.119
IS THAT,
LIKE, A SOLDIER THING?

08:37.240 --> 08:39.504
- UH, NO.

08:39.620 --> 08:41.269
I'M INCREDIBLY NERVOUS,
AND IF I DON'T

08:41.380 --> 08:43.473
JUST COWBOY UP,
THEN I'M GONNA LOSE MY NERVE,

08:43.590 --> 08:45.729
SO, UH--

08:45.830 --> 08:49.652
WOULD YOU GO OUT
WITH ME SOMETIME?

08:51.460 --> 08:53.769
- YEAH.
I GUESS.

08:53.870 --> 08:56.805
- NIFTY.
[laughter]

09:01.540 --> 09:03.428
[knocks at door]

09:03.540 --> 09:05.679
- HEY, BUD.

09:07.580 --> 09:11.744
WHAT YA DOIN'?

09:11.860 --> 09:13.999
SO I JUST--I WANTED TO TALK
TO YOU ABOUT TOMORROW.

09:14.100 --> 09:16.682
UM, DAD AND
I ARE SO INCREDIBLY BUMMED

09:16.790 --> 09:18.758
THAT WE'RE GONNA
MISS YOUR SPEECH.

09:18.860 --> 09:19.588
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.
- IT'S OKAY.

09:19.690 --> 09:22.932
YOU COULDN'T VOTE ANYWAY.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.268
- THAT'S TRUE.
WE CAN'T VOTE,

09:24.390 --> 09:26.836
BUT I REALLY WANTED TO BE THERE
TO SUPPORT YOU.

09:26.940 --> 09:28.862
HAVE YOU THOUGHT ABOUT WHAT YOU
WANT TO SAY TO THE KIDS?

09:28.980 --> 09:32.598
DO YOU HAVE YOUR NOTE CARDS
ALL DONE?

09:32.710 --> 09:35.497
THINGS LIKE THAT?
WHAT YOU WANNA GET ACROSS...

09:35.600 --> 09:37.044
- YEP.
- TO THE STUDENT BODY?

09:37.160 --> 09:38.252
GREAT.

09:38.370 --> 09:40.429
WELL, IF YOU WANT,
I MEAN, I'D LOVE TO HEAR IT.

09:40.540 --> 09:41.916
I WOULD LOVE TO HEAR IT.
I COULD GIVE YOU

09:42.020 --> 09:43.783
SOME POSITIVE FEEDBACK,
OR I CAN JUST READ IT MYSELF.

09:43.890 --> 09:45.926
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO RECITE IT TO ME

09:46.030 --> 09:48.169
IN CASE YOU GET NERVOUS--
- IT'S NOT WRITTEN DOWN.

09:48.270 --> 09:50.374
IT'S IN MY HEAD.

09:50.480 --> 09:53.415
IT'S A SPEECH.
- WHAT'S IN YOUR--

09:53.520 --> 09:55.033
YOU DID--[clears throat]
NOTHING'S--

09:55.140 --> 09:57.062
- YOU DIDN'T
WRITE ANYTHING DOWN AT ALL?

09:57.180 --> 09:58.693
- NOPE.
- MAX?

09:58.800 --> 10:00.552
- [tapping pencil on pad]

10:00.660 --> 10:01.456
- OKAY.

10:01.560 --> 10:03.937
HEY, BUDDY,

10:04.050 --> 10:06.837
SOMETIMES, WHEN YOU
GET UP THERE,

10:06.950 --> 10:08.872
YOU THINK YOU HAVE IT
IN YOUR HEAD,

10:08.980 --> 10:11.676
AND I KNOW THIS
FROM EXPERIENCE.

10:11.780 --> 10:13.941
YOU GET A LITTLE FLUSTERED,
AND YOU SEE THE CROWD,

10:14.060 --> 10:15.049
AND YOU MAY
GET A LITTLE NERVOUS.

10:15.160 --> 10:17.469
AND PEOPLE ARE NOISY
AND VERY RUDE.

10:17.580 --> 10:20.026
THEY DON'T GIVE YOU THE COURTESY
OF GE'I'I'ING YOUR POINT ACROSS.

10:20.130 --> 10:24.510
SO I THINK MAYBE YOU SHOULD
WRITE IT DOWN.

10:24.620 --> 10:26.895
SO WHAT DO YOU SAY?

10:27.000 --> 10:29.685
- I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT
MY SPEECH ANYMORE.

10:29.800 --> 10:31.176
- WILL YOU WRITE DOWN
YOUR NOTES?

10:31.280 --> 10:33.999
I CAN HELP YOU WRITE THEM.
I WROTE FOR BOB LITTLE.

10:34.110 --> 10:35.247
- HE DIDN'T WIN.

10:39.120 --> 10:41.839
- NO, HE DIDN'T.

10:41.950 --> 10:43.838
- THIS'LL BE NICE,
DON'T YOU THINK?

10:43.950 --> 10:45.258
WE GOT SOME MORE STUFF
CLEARED OUT,

10:45.360 --> 10:49.251
AND IT'S A LITTLE BIGGER
THAN YOUR ROOM AT GRANDMA'S.

10:49.370 --> 10:50.746
- YEAH.

10:50.850 --> 10:52.192
- DO YOU NEED HELP UNPACKING?

10:52.300 --> 10:53.403
WE HAVE ONE DRESSER HERE.

10:53.510 --> 10:54.431
- NO, I'M NOT UNPACKING.

10:54.550 --> 10:55.676
I'M JUST LOOKING
FOR A SWEATSHIRT.

10:55.790 --> 10:57.018
I WAS GONNA GO OUT.

10:57.130 --> 10:59.439
- OKAY.

10:59.550 --> 11:02.030
UH, IT'S OUR
FIRST NIGHT HERE,

11:02.140 --> 11:03.755
AND WE WERE SEE; OF THINKING...

11:03.870 --> 11:05.030
- WE'D ALL HANG OUT.

11:05.140 --> 11:06.243
- HOW'S IT ALL GOING?
- GOOD.

11:06.350 --> 11:07.248
- IT'S FINE.

11:07.350 --> 11:09.454
- I CLEANED OUT A DRAWER
IN THE BATHROOM

11:09.560 --> 11:11.039
SO THAT CAN BE YOURS,
AND--

11:11.150 --> 11:13.038
- WE EACH HAVE A DRAWER.
- THAT'S FINE.

11:13.150 --> 11:14.139
I'LL JUST KEEP IT
ALL IN HERE.

11:14.250 --> 11:16.047
- AND ALSO,
I FOUND THE DRILL.

11:16.150 --> 11:17.947
SO IF YOU NEED HELP HANGING
ANYTHING--

11:18.050 --> 11:19.017
- GREAT--OR TAKING
ANYTHING DOWN,

11:19.120 --> 11:20.940
LIKE THE GAS CHART.
- OH, YEAH.

11:21.050 --> 11:23.189
YOU DON'T NEED THAT
GERMAN GAS POSTER.

11:23.300 --> 11:24.699
IF YOU DON'T LIKE IT.
IF YOU LIKE IT,

11:24.820 --> 11:25.741
THAT'S--THAT CAN STAY.

11:25.850 --> 11:28.330
- MOM, CAN I BORROW THE CAR?

11:28.440 --> 11:29.475
- HONEY,
IT'S OUR FIRST NIGHT.

11:29.580 --> 11:30.615
WE WERE GONNA
ORDER SOME FOOD AND,

11:30.720 --> 11:31.926
YOU KNOW, BE TOGETHER.

11:32.030 --> 11:34.476
- I ALREADY
MADE PLANS, LIKE--

11:34.590 --> 11:35.784
- OKAY.

11:35.900 --> 11:37.208
- DO YOU WANT TO EAT
BEFORE WE--

11:37.310 --> 11:38.925
WE GO, OR--
- NO, WE'RE GOING TO EAT.

11:39.040 --> 11:41.656
AND DON'T WORRY ABOUT THE CAR.

11:41.770 --> 11:42.509
I'LL JUST GET SOMEONE
TO PICK ME UP.

11:42.630 --> 11:44.939
- HEY...

11:45.040 --> 11:47.383
DREW...

11:47.490 --> 11:49.663
DREW.

11:49.770 --> 11:51.328
- WHAT, MOM?
- DREW!

11:51.430 --> 11:52.499
[door slams]

11:52.600 --> 11:54.249
- SOMEONE CAN DRIVE ME.
IT'S FINE.

11:54.360 --> 11:55.292
- HONEY, I'M SORRY IF THIS
DOESN'T FEEL GOOD TO YOU.

11:55.400 --> 11:57.743
IT'S JUST NEW, YOU KNOW?
YOU'LL--IT'LL--

11:57.850 --> 11:59.636
- YEAH.
- MARK LOVES YOU.

11:59.750 --> 12:00.671
AND--AND--
- ALL RIGHT, I MEAN,

12:00.780 --> 12:02.509
IT HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH MARK.

12:02.610 --> 12:04.749
HE'S GREAT.
HE'S SUPER NICE.

12:04.860 --> 12:07.499
IT'S JUST--LIKE, YOU PICK UP
AND MOVE ME

12:07.620 --> 12:08.894
IN THE MIDDLE
OF MY SENIOR YEAR,

12:09.000 --> 12:10.683
AND, YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA
BE MOVING AGAIN SOON.

12:10.790 --> 12:12.826
AND, IT JUST SUCKS.

12:12.930 --> 12:14.932
NOW I LIVE WITH MR. CYR,
LIKE A TEACHER.

12:15.040 --> 12:16.268
- HE'S NOT MR. CYR.
HE'S GONNA BE YOUR STEPFATHER.

12:16.390 --> 12:19.382
AND THIS WAY, WHEN YOU COME
BACK FROM COLLEGE,

12:19.490 --> 12:21.799
THIS WILL ALREADY
FEEL LIKE HOME, YOU KNOW?

12:21.910 --> 12:23.764
- OKAY, YOU DIDN'T
THINK ABOUT THAT

12:23.880 --> 12:24.972
WHEN YOU FIRST MADE
THIS DECISION, YOU KNOW.

12:25.080 --> 12:26.593
- YES, I DID.
- NOW YOU'RE PIECING IT TOGETHER

12:26.710 --> 12:27.938
BUT--
- I THOUGHT YOU WOULD BE HAPPY.

12:28.050 --> 12:29.847
YOU KNOW?
- NO, YOU LITERALLY

12:29.950 --> 12:31.394
MADE THE DECISION AND TOLD ME
THAT I'M MOVING.

12:31.500 --> 12:33.081
LIKE, YOU DIDN'T EVEN
THINK ABOUT ME AT ALL.

12:44.380 --> 12:46.109
- HEY, LISTEN, I SPOKE
TO ADAM THIS MORNING,

12:46.210 --> 12:46.995
AND HE SAID THAT HE'D PREFER
NOT TO HAVE A BIG CROWD

12:47.110 --> 12:48.418
IN THE WAITING ROOM
TOMORROW.

12:48.520 --> 12:51.557
SO I'VE MADE UP
A SCHEDULE FOR ALL OF US.

12:51.660 --> 12:53.104
WHERE ARE YOU?

12:53.220 --> 12:56.451
- UH, I AM AT THE DOG PARK
BEING SUPER HELPFUL

12:56.560 --> 12:57.731
AND WALKING OTIS.

12:57.840 --> 12:59.660
I'M ALSO PICKING UP
SOME PRE-SURGERY DINNER.

12:59.770 --> 13:01.328
- GOOD FOR YOU.

13:01.430 --> 13:03.773
OKAY, SO DO YOU WANT
THE 6:00 TO 8:00 A.M. SHIFT,

13:03.880 --> 13:05.916
THE 8:00 TO 10:00 A.M.,
OR THE 10:00 TO NOON?

13:06.020 --> 13:07.089
AFTER 12:00, THE ROTATION
STARTS OVER.

13:07.200 --> 13:10.533
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
TWO-HOUR SHIFTS?

13:10.650 --> 13:11.571
I'M NOT DOING THAT.

13:11.680 --> 13:13.056
- WELL, IT'S WHAT ADAM WANTS.

13:13.170 --> 13:14.717
SO WHICH ONE
DO YOU WANT?

13:14.820 --> 13:15.957
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
THIS IS CRAP.

13:16.070 --> 13:17.230
I'M JUST GONNA BE THERE
THE ENTIRE TIME

13:17.340 --> 13:18.614
AND THEY'RE GONNA
HAVE TO DEAL WITH IT.

13:18.720 --> 13:20.062
- CROSBY, THAT'S REALLY
SWEET OF YOU,

13:20.170 --> 13:21.239
BUT THAT JUST MEANS
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU

13:21.350 --> 13:22.510
WHICHEVER ONE
SARAH DOESN'T WANT,

13:22.620 --> 13:24.201
SO LET ME
CONFERENCE HER IN.

13:24.320 --> 13:26.834
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO DO THAT
FROM HOME, I DON'T THINK.

13:26.940 --> 13:27.588
- WHAT?

13:27.700 --> 13:30.043
NO--WHOA! WHOA!

13:30.150 --> 13:32.243
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!
[dog yelps]

13:32.360 --> 13:34.078
[static]

13:39.740 --> 13:41.128
- HEY.

13:41.230 --> 13:43.152
DO YOU NEED HELP WITH SOMETHING?
- HEY, UM--

13:43.270 --> 13:46.125
YEAH.
HOW DOES THIS WORK, EXACTLY?

13:46.230 --> 13:48.437
- OH! I DON'T--
I DON'T HAVE CABLE.

13:48.550 --> 13:50.757
- WHAT?

13:50.860 --> 13:52.589
_ UH--
- FOR REAL?

13:52.690 --> 13:53.964
- YEAH.
HEH, YEAH.

13:54.070 --> 13:56.209
I KNOW, IT'S SUPER LAME.
I HAD IT FOR A LITTLE WHILE,

13:56.310 --> 13:58.175
BUT I WASN'T READING
ANY OF MY BOOKS,

13:58.280 --> 13:59.486
AND I WAS WATCHING
A WHOLE BUNCH OF NOTHING.

13:59.590 --> 14:01.410
SO I FELT LIKE I WAS
BETTER OFF WITHOUT IT.

14:01.530 --> 14:05.114
BUT I DO HAVE A DVD PLAYER.
UH, IF YOU WANT, I--

14:05.220 --> 14:07.563
- IT'S FINE, I CAN JUST,
YOU KNOW, READ A BOOK,

14:07.670 --> 14:08.568
LIKE YOU SAID.

14:08.670 --> 14:12.390
- HEY, UM--

14:12.500 --> 14:15.060
IF--IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I CAN DO TO--

14:15.160 --> 14:17.367
TO HELP MAKE YOU
MORE COMFORTABLE.

14:17.470 --> 14:18.698
IF YOU NEED SOMETHING
FOR YOUR ROOM,

14:18.820 --> 14:21.436
OR IF YOU JUST
WANT SOME MORE PRIVACY.

14:21.550 --> 14:25.065
- YEAH, PRIVACY'S
PROBABLY GOOD, SO--

14:25.170 --> 14:27.229
- OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, COOL.

14:27.340 --> 14:28.307
- ALL RIGHT.

14:37.420 --> 14:38.899
- HEY. UH...

14:39.010 --> 14:40.113
- HEY.
- CROSBY CALLED.

14:40.220 --> 14:42.905
APPARENTLY THERE
WAS SOME INCIDENT WITH OTIS.

14:43.020 --> 14:45.011
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
AN INCIDENT WITH OTIS?

14:45.120 --> 14:46.530
WHAT HAPPENED?
- I'M SURE HE'S FINE, HONEY.

14:46.640 --> 14:48.323
CROSBY SAID HE WAS GONNA
"TOTES HANDLE IT,"

14:48.430 --> 14:49.294
UH, BUT...
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.

14:49.400 --> 14:50.606
- DINNER MIGHT BE
A LITTLE LATE.

14:50.710 --> 14:51.916
- "TOTES HANDLE IT."
WAIT--THIS--OKAY, OVER HERE.

14:52.020 --> 14:53.988
WHAT DO YOU THINK SO FAR?

14:54.100 --> 14:54.987
- I THINK IT LOOKS GREAT.

14:55.100 --> 14:56.055
- GOOD, I HAVEN'T USED THIS--

14:56.170 --> 14:57.546
- YOU LOOK REALLY PRETTY.

14:57.650 --> 14:58.856
YOU'RE USING THE GOOD PLATES.
- THANK YOU.

14:58.960 --> 15:00.928
YEAH, AND I'M USING
THE GOOD SILVERWARE

15:01.030 --> 15:02.133
WE HAVEN'T USED IN AGES,

15:02.240 --> 15:03.719
SO I THOUGHT I MIGHT AS WELL
PULL IT OUT

15:03.830 --> 15:04.854
AND, YOU KNOW,
HAVE SOME FUN WITH IT.

15:04.970 --> 15:06.176
SORT OF SEIZE THE MOMENT.

15:06.280 --> 15:07.099
- CAN I GIVE YOU A HAND
WITH THOSE NAPKINS?

15:07.210 --> 15:08.279
- NOPE, I GOT IT.
- OKAY.

15:08.390 --> 15:10.312
- EVERYTHING'S UNDER CONTROL.
I JUST...

15:10.420 --> 15:12.866
WANT TO SORT OF TAKE MY MIND
OFF OF THINGS.

15:12.980 --> 15:15.380
THAT ONE NEEDS A FORK,
BUT--

15:15.500 --> 15:18.879
[sighs] SO I WANTED
TO ASK YOU A QUESTION.

15:18.980 --> 15:20.254
- WHAT?

15:20.360 --> 15:22.737
- OKAY, WELL, I TALKED TO MAX
ABOUT HIS SPEECH.

15:22.850 --> 15:24.568
- AND?
- TURNS OUT

15:24.680 --> 15:26.500
HE HAS NOTHING PREPARED.

15:26.610 --> 15:28.157
LIKE, ADAM, ZERO.

15:28.270 --> 15:30.124
HE DIDN'T WRITE DOWN
A STINKIN' THING.

15:30.230 --> 15:32.300
- OKAY. I WILL--I WILL
DEAL WITH HIM AFTER DINNER.

15:32.410 --> 15:33.195
ALL RIGHT? WE'LL MAKE SURE
HE HAS SOMETHING FOR TOMORROW.

15:33.310 --> 15:36.609
- OKAY.
I HAVE ANOTHER IDEA.

15:36.720 --> 15:37.994
- HMM.
- WHAT IF, AFTER YOU

15:38.100 --> 15:39.510
CHECK ME IN
AT THE HOSPITAL,

15:39.620 --> 15:42.032
YOU WHIZ OVER THERE
REALLY QUICKLY,

15:42.140 --> 15:44.517
AND CHECK ON HIM,
MAKE SURE HE'S GOOD.

15:44.630 --> 15:45.790
- KRISTINA, I CAN'T.
- I AM OUT TO LUNCH.

15:45.910 --> 15:48.174
- I'M DRUGGED UP.
I'M UNCONSCIOUS, BABE.

15:48.290 --> 15:49.552
- I CAN'T LEAVE YOU
AT THE HOSPITAL.

15:49.670 --> 15:50.420
- YOU'RE JUST GONNA BE
SITTING IN THE WAITING ROOM,

15:50.530 --> 15:52.009
READING A MAGAZINE, SO--

15:52.120 --> 15:53.144
- MAYBE MY DAD CAN GO.

15:53.260 --> 15:54.352
- YOUR DAD?
- WHAT?

15:54.470 --> 15:55.323
- LORD KNOWS WHAT--
- NO, I'LL DO IT.

16:00.640 --> 16:03.291
- [sighs]

16:03.410 --> 16:06.504
- THANK YOU, HADDIE.
- THANK YOU.

16:06.620 --> 16:09.305
[indistinct chatter]

16:09.410 --> 16:11.025
- SO HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN--
- SO YOU'RE FROM--

16:11.140 --> 16:13.540
I'M SORRY. YOU GO.
YOU GO AHEAD.

16:13.660 --> 16:16.345
- UH, NO, I WAS JUST GONNA--

16:16.450 --> 16:18.418
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
WORKED WITH YOUR UNCLES?

16:18.520 --> 16:18.895
- OH, UM...

16:19.010 --> 16:21.001
NOT THAT LONG.

16:21.110 --> 16:22.452
A LITTLE WHILE.
YEAH, BUT IT'S FUN.

16:22.560 --> 16:23.936
- COOL.
- UM...

16:24.050 --> 16:26.564
BEFORE THAT, ACTUALLY,
I WORKED WITH MY AUNT

16:26.670 --> 16:28.114
ON A--
ON AN ELECTION.

16:28.220 --> 16:28.777
- OH, NICE.
- YEAH, HEH.

16:28.880 --> 16:30.916
UH, WE LOST.

16:31.020 --> 16:33.227
BUT THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

16:33.330 --> 16:35.844
THE JOURNEY WAS AMAZING.
IT WAS REALLY FUN AND,

16:35.960 --> 16:38.918
YOU KNOW, UM,

16:39.030 --> 16:41.749
WE JUST WORKED WELL
TOGETHER AND STUFF, SO--

16:41.860 --> 16:43.999
- YOU MUST BE REALLY CLOSE.

16:44.100 --> 16:45.715
- MM-HMM.

16:47.900 --> 16:49.868
- THAT'S NICE.

16:49.970 --> 16:52.074
- SO...

16:52.180 --> 16:54.933
WHAT ARE WE GONNA GET?

16:55.040 --> 16:55.972
- I HOPE
YOU DON'T FEEL LIKE

16:56.080 --> 16:57.354
YOU HAD TO GO OUT ON A DATE
WITH ME.

16:57.460 --> 17:00.008
LIKE, IT WOULD BE RUDE
TO YOUR GRANDPA OR SOMETHING

17:00.120 --> 17:01.257
IF YOU SAID NO.

17:01.360 --> 17:04.944
- NO, RYAN,
I DON'T FEEL LIKE THAT.

17:05.050 --> 17:05.948
- IT JUST KIND OF
SEEMS LIKE...

17:06.050 --> 17:08.052
YOU'RE NOT REALLY INTO IT.

17:08.160 --> 17:09.320
WHICH IS--
WHICH IS TOTALLY FINE.

17:09.440 --> 17:11.158
- NO. GOD.

17:11.270 --> 17:12.362
IT'S NOT THAT.

17:12.470 --> 17:14.745
UM...

17:14.860 --> 17:16.475
I THINK I'M FEELING
DISTRACTED

17:16.580 --> 17:18.684
BECAUSE IT'S, UH,

17:18.790 --> 17:22.419
IT'S MY AUNT'S, LIKE,
SURGERY THINGY TOMORROW.

17:22.520 --> 17:23.726
- OH.
- I WAS JUST THINKING ABOUT HER.

17:23.830 --> 17:26.799
AND THEN I JUST REALIZED
THAT I THINK I'VE BEEN

17:26.900 --> 17:29.209
NOT REALLY
DEALING WITH IT, AND...

17:29.320 --> 17:31.174
[crying] I ACTUALLY
FEEL KIND OF SCARED,

17:31.290 --> 17:34.043
'CAUSE I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN AND--

17:34.150 --> 17:36.141
I'M SORRY,
I'M GETTING EMOTIONAL...

17:36.260 --> 17:37.943
- NO, HERE.
- ON OUR FIRST--

17:38.050 --> 17:40.291
FIRST DATE,
SO THAT'S NOT GOOD.

17:40.400 --> 17:43.563
I UNDERSTAND IF THIS IS
JUST TOO HEAW

17:43.680 --> 17:44.954
AND YOU'D RATHER NOT--

17:45.060 --> 17:47.119
- OH, NO.
NO, NO.

17:47.230 --> 17:48.879
I MEAN, IF YOU
WANT TO GO HOME,

17:48.990 --> 17:50.571
I WILL TAKE YOU HOME
RIGHT NOW.

17:50.690 --> 17:53.022
BUT I--BUT IT'S NOT--
IT'S NOT TOO HEAW.

17:53.140 --> 17:55.540
YOU KNOW, I WOULD LOVE
TO BUY YOU A BURRITO

17:55.660 --> 17:57.799
AND TALK SOME MORE
ABOUT YOUR AUNT.

17:57.900 --> 17:59.583
IF THAT'S OKAY.

17:59.690 --> 18:01.317
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

18:01.420 --> 18:01.966
HOW DO YOU KNOW HER?

18:02.080 --> 18:03.832
[both laugh]

18:03.940 --> 18:05.999
THAT WAS FUNNY.

18:06.110 --> 18:07.691
- WHAT'S SHE LIKE?

18:07.810 --> 18:09.141
- AH...

18:09.260 --> 18:10.591
SHE'S GREAT.

18:10.710 --> 18:12.280
MY MOM'S ALWAYS TRYING
TO GET ME TO GET

18:12.400 --> 18:14.015
A STRONGER LOCK,
BUT, YOU KNOW,

18:14.120 --> 18:16.680
THIS ONE DOES THE TRICK,
SO...

18:16.780 --> 18:18.429
[sighs]

18:18.540 --> 18:18.881
UH...OKAY.

18:18.990 --> 18:21.959
WELL...

18:22.060 --> 18:23.095
THAT WAS GREAT.
THANK YOU.

18:23.200 --> 18:25.782
- YEAH.
- IT WAS REALLY HELPFUL TOO.

18:25.890 --> 18:29.337
- I'M REALLY GLAD THAT WE
COULD GET TOGETHER.

18:30.410 --> 18:33.345
- UM...DO YOU WANNA COME IN?

18:33.450 --> 18:38.035
- I-I THINK I BETTER
GET GOING.

18:38.150 --> 18:38.900
- OH. OKAY.

18:39.010 --> 18:40.898
YEAH, I MEAN, I...

18:41.010 --> 18:43.319
SHOULD SLEEP.

18:43.430 --> 18:44.499
BECAUSE SLEEPING'S IMPORTANT.

18:44.600 --> 18:46.807
- YEAH, ME TOO.
- SO...

18:46.910 --> 18:50.630
- WELL, I'LL BE THINKING
ABOUT YOUR AUNT TOMORROW.

18:50.750 --> 18:51.774
GOOD NIGHT.

18:51.880 --> 18:52.744
- GOOD NIGHT.

19:05.480 --> 19:08.415
- MAYBE WE SHOULD
CALL UNCLE CROSBY AGAIN.

19:08.520 --> 19:09.691
- HE SAID HE WAS GONNA BE HERE
IN TEN MINUTES.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.279
- YEAH, HE SAID THAT
A HALF HOUR AGO.

19:11.390 --> 19:12.459
- HADDIE, HE KNOWS
THAT YOUR MOTHER

19:12.560 --> 19:15.211
CAN'T EAT OR DRINK ANYTHING
AFTER 8:00.

19:15.320 --> 19:16.594
SO HE'LL BE HERE.
- OKAY.

19:16.700 --> 19:17.667
- YOU KNOW, IF YOU EAT SOMETHING
BEFORE YOUR SURGERY,

19:17.770 --> 19:19.328
YOU CAN THROW UP
IN YOUR BREATHING TUBE

19:19.430 --> 19:19.942
AND THEN INHALE IT
INTO YOUR LUNGS.

19:20.050 --> 19:22.018
- MAX...STOP.

19:22.120 --> 19:23.257
- IF THAT EVER HAPPENS
TO YOU,

19:23.360 --> 19:25.248
IT'S 100% DEATH RATE.
- OKAY, STOP.

19:25.370 --> 19:26.564
- MAX, THAT'S ENOUGH.
- GREAT. WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

19:26.680 --> 19:28.466
- THERE'S NO WAY TO SAVE THEM.
- WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

19:28.580 --> 19:29.672
- I AM GONNA CALL CROSBY.

19:29.780 --> 19:31.168
- I'M GONNA MAKE MYSELF
A SANDWICH.

19:31.270 --> 19:32.430
THIS IS GETTING
KIND OF SILLY.

19:32.550 --> 19:34.233
I WANT THEM TO EAT,
YOU KNOW?

19:34.340 --> 19:36.786
'CAUSE, LIKE, THEY'VE BEEN
SITTING HERE FOR SO LONG.

19:36.890 --> 19:38.164
