- ALL RIGHT, WE GOTTA EAT.

20:48.000 --> 20:49.888
I'M GONNA GET THIS READY.
- WHAT DO YOU WANT?

20:50.000 --> 20:51.069
- I GOT IT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

20:51.180 --> 20:52.204
- ALL RIGHT.
- OTIS.

20:52.320 --> 20:54.379
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR BRINGING EVERYTHING.

20:54.490 --> 20:56.765
- I'M SORRY.
- THAT'S OKAY.

20:56.870 --> 20:59.976
- DO A GOOD JOB TOMORROW.

21:00.080 --> 21:02.640
- I WILL.

21:02.740 --> 21:04.423
THANK YOU.

21:04.530 --> 21:05.633
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

21:13.750 --> 21:14.785
- OKAY.

21:14.890 --> 21:17.051
NOW LET'S GIVE THIS BUNNY
A NIGHT-NIGHT KISS.

21:17.170 --> 21:18.398
[gaSPSJ
HERE, BUNNY.

21:18.510 --> 21:19.681
NIGHT-NIGHT KISS.

21:19.790 --> 21:20.859
MWAH.

21:20.960 --> 21:22.848
[gasps] MWAH.

21:22.970 --> 21:24.062
NOW, NORA,

21:24.170 --> 21:27.242
MAMA'S GONNA PUT YOU
BACK IN, OKAY?

21:27.350 --> 21:28.442
LET'S GO NIGHT-NIGHT.

21:28.560 --> 21:29.549
[kiss kiss]
- MAMA.

21:29.660 --> 21:32.549
- MAMA LOVES YOU, OKAY?
- MOMMY?

21:32.670 --> 21:37.209
- I KNOW, I KNOW,
I KNOW, I KNOW.

21:37.330 --> 21:39.218
MOMMY LOVES YOU.

21:39.330 --> 21:40.661
[whines]

21:53.790 --> 21:55.758
[sighs]

21:59.170 --> 22:01.138
- RIGHT. YEAH.

22:01.250 --> 22:02.933
THAT'S WHAT
I WAS THINKING TOO.

22:03.040 --> 22:04.689
OKAY.

22:04.800 --> 22:06.904
UM...
- HI.

22:07.010 --> 22:07.795
- GREAT. THAN KS.

22:07.910 --> 22:09.172
THEN I WILL JUST
TALK TO YOU LATER.

22:09.290 --> 22:12.396
THANK YOU. BYE.

22:12.500 --> 22:13.728
- WHO WERE YOU TALKING TO?

22:13.840 --> 22:18.493
- UM, TO THE DEAN'S OFFICE
AT CORNELL.

22:18.610 --> 22:21.261
AND, UH, THEY WERE ACTUALLY
BEING REALLY HELPFUL

22:21.370 --> 22:23.600
AND REALLY UNDERSTANDING.
- ABOUT?

22:23.720 --> 22:25.574
- THIS KIND OF SITUATION
HAPPENS A LOT, ACTUALLY, UM--

22:25.680 --> 22:28.399
- OKAY, HOLD ON A SECOND.
- THE THING IS--

22:28.510 --> 22:30.068
- WE'VE TALKED ABOUT THIS,
HADDIE.

22:30.170 --> 22:31.137
- I KNOW, BUT HANG ON, JUST--
- YOU'RE GOING BACK TO SCHOOL.

22:31.240 --> 22:32.343
- JUST HANG ON.
JUST LISTEN.

22:32.450 --> 22:34.657
WE CAN GET THE WHOLE
FIRST SEMESTER REFUNDED.

22:34.760 --> 22:37.172
LIKE, BECAUSE IT'S
A MEDICAL ISSUE.

22:37.280 --> 22:38.793
IT INCLUDES HOUSING...
- CAN YOU PLEASE TELL HER--

22:38.900 --> 22:42.529
- AND THAT MEANS THAT I CAN
JUST GO INTO SPRING SEMESTER--

22:42.630 --> 22:43.733
- HADDIE...
- NO, ABSOLUTELY NOT.

22:43.840 --> 22:44.738
- IT'S FINE.
- IT'S NICE OF YOU TO OFFER,

22:44.840 --> 22:46.000
BUT YOU'RE STAYING IN SCHOOL.

22:46.120 --> 22:47.394
- I'M GOING TO BE FINE.

22:47.500 --> 22:49.286
THIS IS A MINOR OPERATION,
OKAY?

22:49.400 --> 22:50.628
IT'S A VERY SMALL TUMOR.
- SURE.

22:50.740 --> 22:52.082
- I TOLD YOU WHAT
THE DOCTOR SAID.

22:52.190 --> 22:53.179
- THERE'S, LIKE, A LOT OF STUFF
THAT HAS TO GET DONE

22:53.300 --> 22:54.574
AROUND HERE THAT WOULD
- I KNOW.

22:54.680 --> 22:56.261
BUT I'M GONNA BE FINE.
- BE NICE TO HAVE HELP WITH.

22:56.370 --> 22:57.746
- HADDIE, I AM GOING
TO BE FINE.

22:57.850 --> 22:58.782
- OKAY, LISTEN,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

22:58.890 --> 23:00.232
WE CAN TALK ABOUT THIS LATER.

23:00.340 --> 23:01.546
THEY TOLD US NOT TO BE LATE,
HONEY.

23:01.650 --> 23:02.571
WE GOTTA GET GOING.
- I KNOW, I KNOW.

23:02.690 --> 23:04.578
I JUST WANTED TO--
I'M JUST GONNA--

23:04.690 --> 23:07.341
OKAY, WE'LL
DISCUSS THIS LATER.

23:07.450 --> 23:09.065
UM, AS FOR TODAY,

23:09.180 --> 23:11.341
MAX HAS HIS SPEECH.

23:11.450 --> 23:12.826
MAKE SURE THAT HE WEARS
A CLEAN T-SHIRT,

23:12.940 --> 23:14.862
BECAUSE HE'S GONNA BE
IN FRONT OF ALL THOSE KIDS,

23:14.970 --> 23:16.699
AND, LIKE,
I DON'T WANT HIM...

23:16.800 --> 23:19.109
[crying] WEARING THAT SAME
RATTY T-SHIRT.

23:19.220 --> 23:20.903
IT'S SO--

23:21.020 --> 23:22.635
- I LOVE YOU.

23:23.880 --> 23:27.566
- I LOVE YOU.
AND WE'RE GONNA BE FINE.

23:27.680 --> 23:30.228
- MM-HMM.
- OKAY.

23:30.330 --> 23:32.093
- OKAY?
- OKAY.

23:32.200 --> 23:32.712
- BYE.

23:39.170 --> 23:39.682
[door opens]

23:44.590 --> 23:44.794
[door closes]

23:50.530 --> 23:52.623
[door opens]

23:52.740 --> 23:54.253
- HI. GOOD MORNING.
- HEY.

23:54.360 --> 23:56.499
WHAT'S UP?
HOW ARE YOU?

23:56.600 --> 23:59.182
- GETTIN' CHILLY OUT THERE.

23:59.290 --> 24:00.632
LATTE, EXTRA HOT TODAY.

24:00.740 --> 24:01.672
- CAFFEINE, RIGHT?

24:01.780 --> 24:03.361
- YES.
- DOUBLE SUGAR?

24:03.470 --> 24:06.189
- THERE'S ALL THE FIXINS.
- YEAH.

24:06.300 --> 24:07.710
I'M GONNA NEED THAT LATER.

24:07.820 --> 24:09.469
I FEEL A CRASH COMIN'.
- YOU DO?

24:09.580 --> 24:10.615
- AH, I'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

24:10.720 --> 24:12.164
HEY, HOW'D THE MOVE GO?

24:12.270 --> 24:14.022
- GOOD. JUST, YOU KNOW,
MOVING.

24:14.140 --> 24:16.472
- HOW ABOUT DREW?
BOY, WHAT WAS UP WITH HIM?

24:16.590 --> 24:17.750
I THOUGHT I WAS GRUMPY.

24:17.870 --> 24:19.371
- [chuckles]

24:19.490 --> 24:20.889
- HE ALMOST TOOK
A BUSH OUT THERE.

24:21.010 --> 24:21.829
- YEAH, HE DID.

24:21.940 --> 24:23.862
WE HAD TALKED ABOUT
DIFFERENT DATES,

24:23.970 --> 24:26.279
AND HE DIDN'T LIKE
THE ONE WE PICKED, SO...

24:26.390 --> 24:27.527
- WHAT HAPPENED?
YOU MOVE THAT UP ON HIM?

24:27.630 --> 24:31.498
- YEAH, WE MOVED IT UP.

24:31.600 --> 24:33.875
JUST, UH...

24:33.980 --> 24:36.084
YOU KNOW, JUST SEEMED LIKE
A GOOD TIME.

24:41.580 --> 24:42.911
- HEY, UH...

24:43.030 --> 24:47.023
DID--IT DIDN'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO WITH--

24:47.140 --> 24:49.893
WITH WHAT I DID, RIGHT?

24:50.000 --> 24:53.379
- NO.

24:53.490 --> 24:56.277
- OKAY, GOOD.

24:56.390 --> 24:58.904
ALL RIGHT.
WELL, THAT'S GOOD.

24:59.010 --> 25:00.386
YOU'RE GONNA
DO BILLING TODAY, RIGHT?

25:00.490 --> 25:02.424
- MM-HMM.

25:02.530 --> 25:03.838
- WE'RE GONNA
NEED SOME CASH.

25:11.710 --> 25:14.599
- ARE YOU NOT TEACHING
FIRST PERIOD TODAY?

25:14.720 --> 25:17.746
- OH, NO, MRS. GRISCOM
IS COVERING MY MORNING CLASSES

25:17.860 --> 25:19.578
SO I CAN WAIT
FOR THE CABLE GUY.

25:19.690 --> 25:21.783
- [chuckles]
YOU'RE GETTING CABLE?

25:21.890 --> 25:22.709
- YEP.

25:22.830 --> 25:23.899
WE ARE GETTING CABLE.

25:27.660 --> 25:28.410
- ALL RIGHTY, WELL...

25:28.520 --> 25:30.579
I GOTTA GET THE BUS.

25:30.700 --> 25:34.761
- ALL RIGHT.
HAVE A GOOD ONE.

25:34.870 --> 25:37.282
- WELL, I'M REALLY GLAD WE
GOT HERE AT THE CRACK OF DAWN.

25:37.390 --> 25:38.630
IT'S VERY HELPFUL
TO SIT AROUND HERE

25:38.740 --> 25:40.526
AND THINK ABOUT SURGERY
FOR HOURS.

25:40.640 --> 25:41.208
DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.
- IT'S PROTOCOL, HONEY.

25:41.330 --> 25:43.707
I KNOW.

25:43.810 --> 25:45.698
- WHAT CAN I GET YOU?
YOU WANT ANOTHER MAGAZINE?

25:45.820 --> 25:48.266
- I'VE READ THEM ALL.

25:48.370 --> 25:50.645
- iPHONE?
WANNA HAVE A LITTLE--

25:50.750 --> 25:52.297
LITTLE TOURNAMENT?

25:52.410 --> 25:53.195
- [laughs] NO
-HUH? '

25:53.310 --> 25:55.710
NO?
- YOU'RE SO WEIRD.

25:55.830 --> 25:57.161
- I'M JUST TRYING.
- I KNOW, I KNOW.

25:57.270 --> 25:58.271
I'M JUST...
- I KNOW.

25:58.380 --> 25:59.927
- THIRSTY.

26:00.040 --> 26:01.689
- WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
ABOUT HADDIE?

26:01.800 --> 26:03.370
- SHE'S GOING BACK TO SCHOOL.

26:03.490 --> 26:04.514
- RIGHT? BACK TO SCHOOL.
- YEAH.

26:04.630 --> 26:06.074
- ALL RIGHT, GOOD.

26:06.180 --> 26:07.977
- THAT'S ALL.

26:08.080 --> 26:11.117
WISH WE COULD CALL
AND FIND OUT HOW MAX IS DOING.

26:11.220 --> 26:13.188
- I'LL CALL HIM LATER, OKAY?
- WILL YOU TEXT HER?

26:13.290 --> 26:14.109
- WHEN YOU FINISH THIS,
I'M GONNA LET YOU KNOW

26:14.220 --> 26:15.084
WHAT'S GOING ON.
- YES.

26:15.190 --> 26:16.805
- ALL RIGHT, WE GOTTA
GET THIS MOVING.

26:16.920 --> 26:18.842
I'M GONNA GO FIND A NURSE.
- I KNOW.

26:20.640 --> 26:21.675
- HI.
- HI.

26:21.780 --> 26:22.883
- MRS. BRAVERMAN,
WE'RE READY FOR YOU.

26:22.990 --> 26:23.911
- AND WE'RE READY FOR YOU.

26:24.030 --> 26:25.474
- I'LL TAKE YOU INTO THE O.R.

26:25.580 --> 26:26.547
MR. BRAVERMAN, AN ORDERLY WILL
SHOW YOU TO THE WAITING ROOM.

26:26.650 --> 26:27.924
- I CAN'T GO TO THE O.R.?

26:28.030 --> 26:30.783
- I'M SORRY.
THEY DON'T ALLOW THAT.

26:30.890 --> 26:33.370
- OH.
- I THOUGHT--

26:33.480 --> 26:36.108
- WHY DON'T I GIVE YOU TWO
A MINUTE?

26:40.180 --> 26:42.239
- I GUESS THIS IS IT.

26:42.350 --> 26:45.456
- YEAH. OKAY.

26:45.560 --> 26:47.255
- [scoffs]
I'VE BEEN SO IMPATIENT.

26:47.360 --> 26:51.603
NOW I DON'T WANT
TO LET YOU GO.

26:51.710 --> 26:52.916
KRISTINA,
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

26:53.020 --> 26:55.500
- I KNOW.
- YOU KNOW THAT?

26:55.610 --> 26:58.295
STRONG.
SO STRONG.

27:00.410 --> 27:01.786
- LET'S JUST GET IT DONE.
- I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

27:01.890 --> 27:02.857
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

27:02.960 --> 27:04.643
WILL YOU EAT, PLEASE?
- I WILL.

27:04.760 --> 27:06.921
- EAT SOMETHING.
- I WILL.

27:07.030 --> 27:08.406
DO YOU WANT ME TO GET YOU
SOMETHING FOR AFTER?

27:08.520 --> 27:09.680
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
- A BURGER.

27:09.800 --> 27:12.268
- BURGER.
- BIG, FAT, JUICY...

27:12.380 --> 27:14.132
CH EESEBURGER.
- ALL RIGHT.

27:14.250 --> 27:15.524
- WITH CHEESE.

27:15.630 --> 27:17.769
- OKAY, A CHEESEBURGER.

27:41.450 --> 27:44.203
[indistinct chatter]

27:47.590 --> 27:49.410
- TWO MINUTES LONGER
THAN LAST TIME.

27:49.520 --> 27:52.557
- AH.

27:52.670 --> 27:53.830
- YOU WANT SOMETHING?

27:53.940 --> 27:55.248
THEY HAVE TEA AND STUFF
OVER HERE.

27:55.360 --> 27:57.043
- NO, I'M OKAY.
- OKAY.

27:57.150 --> 27:58.731
- TEA. EVERYBODY'S BEEN
OFFERING ME TEA.

27:58.840 --> 27:59.977
IT'S FUNNY.

28:00.090 --> 28:01.808
- IT'S SOOTHING, MAYBE?
I DON'T KNOW.

28:01.920 --> 28:04.741
- HEY, LISTEN,
I DIDN'T REALLY

28:04.850 --> 28:06.294
TAKE A CLOSE LOOK
AT THIS BEFORE.

28:06.400 --> 28:08.573
I WANT YOU TO MAKE SURE

28:08.680 --> 28:09.988
TO THANK CINDY AND VICTOR
FOR ME, OKAY?

28:10.100 --> 28:11.886
'CAUSE I'LL PROBABLY FORGET.
IT'S NICE, IT'S REAL NICE.

28:12.000 --> 28:13.615
I'LL MAKE SURE
KRISTINA SEES IT.

28:13.720 --> 28:16.302
SO THANK 'EM.
- I WILL DO THAT.

28:16.410 --> 28:20.414
ACTUALLY, JOEL MADE IT,
SO I WILL THANK HIM FOR YOU.

28:20.520 --> 28:21.589
- OH.
- YEAH.

28:21.700 --> 28:24.100
- NICE WORK, JOEL.
- YES.

28:24.210 --> 28:25.529
THE STAY-AT-HOME PARENT THING,

28:25.630 --> 28:26.858
THE FULL-TIME THING--

28:26.980 --> 28:27.969
HARDER THAN I THOUGHT.

28:28.080 --> 28:31.834
- RIGHT, MOM AND DAD
TOLD ME YOU QUIT.

28:31.950 --> 28:33.804
- YEAH.
- GOD, THAT'S A BIG DEAL.

28:33.910 --> 28:35.559
I'M SORRY I HAVEN'T CALLED.
I'VE JUST BEEN...

28:35.670 --> 28:38.321
- IT'S OKAY.

28:38.440 --> 28:40.089
UM...THIS IS A BIG DEAL.

28:40.200 --> 28:42.407
SO WE DON'T HAVE TO TALK
ABOUT MY THING.

28:42.510 --> 28:44.978
- AH.

28:45.100 --> 28:45.998
[sighs]

28:51.970 --> 28:53.414
WHAT WAS THAT, LIKE,
45 SECONDS?

28:53.520 --> 28:56.375
- MM-HMM.
LITTLE UNDER A MINUTE.

28:56.490 --> 28:59.209
[excited chatter and laughter]

29:03.430 --> 29:04.874
- YOU KNOW, MAX,

29:04.980 --> 29:07.119
THERE ARE ACTUALLY
SOME QUALITIES ABOUT YOU

29:07.220 --> 29:08.494
THAT WOULD MAKE YOU
A GOOD PRESIDENT.

29:08.600 --> 29:10.044
- I KNOW.

29:10.160 --> 29:12.537
- LIKE,
YOU'RE SUPER TENACIOUS,

29:12.640 --> 29:15.268
AND YOU'RE FUNNY.

29:15.370 --> 29:16.644
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
BY TENACIOUS?

29:16.750 --> 29:19.503
- UM, I MEAN YOU DON'T
GIVE UP ON THINGS.

29:19.610 --> 29:21.919
YOU'RE PERSISTENT, AND IF YOU
BELIEVE IN SOMETHING,

29:22.030 --> 29:23.258
YOU FOLLOW THROUGH.

29:23.380 --> 29:25.519
AND, ALSO...

29:25.620 --> 29:26.996
YOU HAVE A GOOD MEMORY.

29:27.110 --> 29:28.793
- UH-HUH.
- IT'S LIKE REALLY SCARY GOOD.

29:28.900 --> 29:30.413
- I KNOW, RIGHT?
- DO YOU REMEMBER YOUR SPEECH?

29:30.520 --> 29:33.557
- OF COURSE I DO--YOU JUST SAID
I HAVE A GOOD MEMORY.

29:33.660 --> 29:35.139
- YEAH.
YOU'RE RIGHT. SORRY.

29:35.250 --> 29:37.070
- I'M GONNA GO JOIN
THE OTHER CANDIDATES NOW.

29:37.180 --> 29:39.831
- OKAY. GOOD LUCK.
- YEP.

29:39.950 --> 29:43.010
- AND, MAX...
UM, IF YOU...

29:43.120 --> 29:45.042
HAPPEN TO GET NERVOUS,

29:45.160 --> 29:46.707
JUST LOOK AT ME, AND I WILL
GIVE YOU A BIG THUMBS UP.

29:46.810 --> 29:48.914
- I WON'T GET NERVOUS.

29:49.020 --> 29:50.533
- OKAY. IF YOU DO...
- I WON'T.

29:50.650 --> 29:52.811
- ALL RIGHT.

29:52.920 --> 29:56.026
[indistinct chatter]

29:58.410 --> 30:00.469
- IS THERE AN ADAM WARD?

30:02.110 --> 30:04.419
- FINALLY.
- THE SURGEON...

30:04.520 --> 30:05.339
- FALSE ALARM.
- YEAH.

30:05.450 --> 30:06.769
WE WERE HERE TWO HOURS
BEFORE THEM.

30:06.870 --> 30:09.657
- OH, THANK YOU,
DOCTOR.

30:09.770 --> 30:10.930
- LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE
GETTING GOOD NEWS.

30:11.050 --> 30:12.620
- YEAH, WELL, GOOD FOR THEM.

30:12.740 --> 30:15.015
GOD.

30:15.120 --> 30:17.805
I COULD LOSE MY MIND.

30:20.190 --> 30:23.637
[sighs]
- DO YOU WANT SOME TEA?

30:23.750 --> 30:24.956
- NO, I DON'T WANT TEA.

30:25.060 --> 30:26.197
WHY DOES EVERYBODY KEEP
ASKING ME IF I WANT TEA?

30:26.300 --> 30:27.289
- I DON'T KNOW.
- SINCE WHEN HAVE BEEN

30:27.410 --> 30:28.718
A TEA DRINKER?
I DON'T LIKE TEA.

30:28.820 --> 30:29.991
I HATE TEA.
- I DIDN'T KNOW ANYBODY ELSE

30:30.100 --> 30:31.089
ASKED YOU IF YOU WANT TEA--
HOW ABOUT COFFEE?

30:31.200 --> 30:32.576
I'M SORRY.
I DON'T WANT COFFEE EITHER.

30:32.690 --> 30:33.099
ALL RIGHT?
I'M SORRY.

30:36.550 --> 30:39.314
YOU KNOW, IF YOU COULD JUST
DO SOMETHING TO HELP ME

30:39.420 --> 30:40.648
TAKE MY MIND OFF IT?

30:40.760 --> 30:42.796
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH YOU.

30:42.910 --> 30:43.695
- REALLY?
- YEAH. AMBER, DREW, WHATEVER.

30:43.800 --> 30:48.316
WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:48.430 --> 30:50.318
- UH, OKAY.

30:50.430 --> 30:50.907
UM...

30:51.020 --> 30:53.079
HANK KISSED ME.

30:53.190 --> 30:54.737
- THE PHOTOGRAPHER HANK?

30:54.850 --> 30:56.010
- SHUH. AT WORK.
- WHAT?

30:56.130 --> 30:59.600
- YES. I JUST--
YOU NEVER KNOW.

30:59.710 --> 31:01.507
- OKAY, WELL, THIS IS GOOD.
GIVE ME SOME MORE.

31:01.610 --> 31:02.986
- REALLY?
- WHAT HAPPENED?

31:03.100 --> 31:05.614
- WE WERE IN THE DARKROOM,
AND WE'RE, LIKE, DEVELOPING.

31:05.720 --> 31:07.449
- IN THE DARKROOM?
WHAT, ARE YOU IN SEVENTH GRADE.

31:07.550 --> 31:08.687
- SHUT UP. NO.

31:08.790 --> 31:10.519
- DID YOU KISS HIM BACK?
- EW! NO.

31:10.620 --> 31:12.269
I MEAN, NOT "EW,"
BUT NO.

31:12.380 --> 31:15.099
I MEAN, I DIDN'T
RECOIL IN HORROR

31:15.210 --> 31:16.893
OR ANYTHING, BUT I...

31:17.010 --> 31:18.216
- DO YOU LIKE THE GUY?

31:18.320 --> 31:19.389
- NO, NO, NO.

31:19.490 --> 31:20.047
